content: <metadata>   <idinfo>     <citation>       <citeinfo>         <origin>City and County of Denver, Community Planning and Development</origin>         <pubdate>20140723</pubdate>         <title>Registered Neighborhood Organizations </title>         <geoform>vector digital data</geoform>       </citeinfo>     </citation>     <descript>       <abstract>Sec. 41-19 of the Revised Municipal Code (RMC) provides that Neighborhood Organizations be informed of actions that may be of interest such as zoning and liquor license hearings. Each organization must comply with the guidelines of the ordinance. The organization must re-register with the city each year.</abstract>       <purpose>This map contains boundaries of Registered Neighborhood Organizations (RNO) for the purposes of identification for notification. The identify feature will display which RNO's are at a certain point or within a defined area. The boundaries do not necessarily coincide with other boundaries that are used for statistical gathering purposes. The boundaries may overlap or bisect each other.</purpose>     </descript>     <status>       <update>As needed</update>     </status>     <spdom>       <bounding>         <westbc>-105.109967</westbc>         <eastbc>-104.599581</eastbc>         <northbc>39.914178</northbc>         <southbc>39.614311</southbc>       </bounding>     </spdom>     <keywords>       <theme>         <themekt>None</themekt>         <themekey>planning</themekey>       </theme>       <theme>         <themekt>ISO 19115 Topic Categories</themekt>         <themekey>boundaries</themekey>         <themekey>society</themekey>       </theme>       <place>         <placekt>None</placekt>         <placekey>Denver</placekey>         <placekey>Denver County</placekey>         <placekey>Colorado</placekey>         <placekey>USA</placekey>       </place>     </keywords>     <accconst>None</accconst>     <useconst>ACCESS CONSTRAINTS:   None.
